{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":658,"text":"So I'd like to start by focusing on"},{"time":3394,"text":"the world's most dangerous animal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5930,"text":"Now, when you talk about dangerous animals,"},{"time":8090,"text":"most people might think of lions or tigers or sharks."},{"time":11137,"text":"But of course the most dangerous animal"},{"time":12814,"text":"is the mosquito."},{"time":14677,"text":"The mosquito has killed more humans"},{"time":16836,"text":"than any other creature in human history."},{"time":19825,"text":"In fact, probably adding them all together,"},{"time":21815,"text":"the mosquito has killed more humans."},{"time":24001,"text":"And the mosquito has killed more humans than wars"},{"time":26660,"text":"and plague."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28359,"text":"And you would think, would you not,"},{"time":30932,"text":"that with all our science, with all our advances in society,"},{"time":34879,"text":"with better towns, better civilizations, better sanitation,"},{"time":39791,"text":"wealth, that we would get better at controlling mosquitos,"},{"time":42991,"text":"and hence reduce this disease."},{"time":45684,"text":"And that's not really the case."},{"time":49026,"text":"If it was the case, we wouldn't have"},{"time":51146,"text":"between 200 and 300 million cases of malaria every year,"},{"time":55733,"text":"and we wouldn't have"},{"time":57458,"text":"a million and a half deaths from malaria,"},{"time":61400,"text":"and we wouldn't have a disease"},{"time":64100,"text":"that was relatively unknown 50 years ago"},{"time":66636,"text":"now suddenly turned into"},{"time":69468,"text":"the largest mosquito-borne virus threat that we have,"},{"time":72700,"text":"and that's called dengue fever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75393,"text":"So 50 years ago, pretty much no one had heard of it,"},{"time":78124,"text":"no one certainly in the European environment."},{"time":81116,"text":"But dengue fever now, according to the World Health Organization,"},{"time":84749,"text":"infects between 50 and 100 million people every year,"},{"time":88236,"text":"so that's equivalent to the whole of the population"},{"time":90572,"text":"of the U.K. being infected every year."},{"time":93500,"text":"Other estimates put that number at roughly double"},{"time":96612,"text":"that number of infections."},{"time":100570,"text":"And dengue fever has grown in speed quite phenomenally."},{"time":105005,"text":"In the last 50 years, the incidence of dengue"},{"time":108055,"text":"has grown thirtyfold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110273,"text":"Now let me tell you a little bit about what dengue fever is,"},{"time":112776,"text":"for those who don't know."},{"time":114364,"text":"Now let's assume you go on holiday."},{"time":116573,"text":"Let's assume you go to the Caribbean,"},{"time":118335,"text":"or you might go to Mexico. You might go to Latin America,"},{"time":120728,"text":"Asia, Africa, anywhere in Saudi Arabia."},{"time":124687,"text":"You might go to India, the Far East."},{"time":126410,"text":"It doesn't really matter. It's the same mosquito,"},{"time":129023,"text":"and it's the same disease. You're at risk."},{"time":131935,"text":"And let's assume you're bitten by a mosquito"},{"time":134611,"text":"that's carrying that virus."},{"time":136172,"text":"Well, you could develop flu-like symptoms."},{"time":139167,"text":"They could be quite mild."},{"time":140945,"text":"You could develop nausea, headache,"},{"time":143046,"text":"your muscles could feel like they're contracting,"},{"time":145485,"text":"and you could actually feel like your bones are breaking."},{"time":149571,"text":"And that's the nickname given to this disease."},{"time":151795,"text":"It's called breakbone fever,"},{"time":153388,"text":"because that's how you can feel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155732,"text":"Now the odd thing is, is that once you've been bitten"},{"time":158669,"text":"by this mosquito, and you've had this disease,"},{"time":160931,"text":"your body develops antibodies,"},{"time":163553,"text":"so if you're bitten again with that strain,"},{"time":167967,"text":"it doesn't affect you."},{"time":169683,"text":"But it's not one virus, it's four,"},{"time":172603,"text":"and the same protection that gives you the antibodies"},{"time":175579,"text":"and protects you from the same virus that you had before"},{"time":178891,"text":"actually makes you much more susceptible to the other three."},{"time":181957,"text":"So the next time you get dengue fever,"},{"time":184692,"text":"if it's a different strain, you're more susceptible,"},{"time":187332,"text":"you're likely to get worse symptoms,"},{"time":189963,"text":"and you're more likely to get the more severe forms,"},{"time":192564,"text":"hemorrhagic fever or shock syndrome."},{"time":195826,"text":"So you don't want dengue once,"},{"time":197245,"text":"and you certainly don't want it again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199986,"text":"So why is it spreading so fast?"},{"time":203269,"text":"And the answer is this thing."},{"time":205365,"text":"This is Aedes aegypti."},{"time":207139,"text":"Now this is a mosquito that came, like its name suggests,"},{"time":210349,"text":"out of North Africa, and it's spread round the world."},{"time":213791,"text":"Now, in fact, a single mosquito will only travel"},{"time":216919,"text":"about 200 yards in its entire life. They don't travel very far."},{"time":220648,"text":"What they're very good at doing is hitchhiking,"},{"time":223033,"text":"particularly the eggs."},{"time":224443,"text":"They will lay their eggs in clear water, any pool, any puddle,"},{"time":229140,"text":"any birdbath, any flower pot,"},{"time":231090,"text":"anywhere there's clear water, they'll lay their eggs,"},{"time":233830,"text":"and if that clear water is near freight, it's near a port,"},{"time":237452,"text":"if it's anywhere near transport,"},{"time":240101,"text":"those eggs will then get transported around the world."},{"time":243285,"text":"And that's what's happened. Mankind has transported"},{"time":245708,"text":"these eggs all the way around the world,"},{"time":247714,"text":"and these insects have infested over 100 countries,"},{"time":251412,"text":"and there's now 2.5 billion people living in countries"},{"time":254110,"text":"where this mosquito resides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257102,"text":"To give you just a couple of examples"},{"time":258686,"text":"how fast this has happened,"},{"time":261202,"text":"in the mid-'70s, Brazil declared, \"We have no Aedes aegypti,\""},{"time":266718,"text":"and currently they spend about a billion dollars now"},{"time":269068,"text":"a year trying to get rid of it, trying to control it,"},{"time":271868,"text":"just one species of mosquito."},{"time":276969,"text":"Two days ago, or yesterday, I can't remember which,"},{"time":280512,"text":"I saw a Reuters report that said"},{"time":282476,"text":"Madeira had had their first cases of dengue,"},{"time":285110,"text":"about 52 cases, with about 400 probable cases."},{"time":288930,"text":"That's two days ago."},{"time":290744,"text":"Interestingly, Madeira first got the insect in 2005,"},{"time":295925,"text":"and here we are, a few years later,"},{"time":297982,"text":"first cases of dengue."},{"time":299309,"text":"So the one thing you'll find is that where the mosquito goes,"},{"time":302668,"text":"dengue will follow."},{"time":304982,"text":"Once you've got the mosquito in your area,"},{"time":307173,"text":"anyone coming into that area with dengue,"},{"time":309542,"text":"mosquito will bite them, mosquito will bite somewhere else,"},{"time":312485,"text":"somewhere else, somewhere else,"},{"time":313449,"text":"and you'll get an epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317564,"text":"So we must be good at killing mosquitos."},{"time":319472,"text":"I mean, that can't be very difficult."},{"time":321369,"text":"Well, there's two principle ways."},{"time":324189,"text":"The first way is that you use larvicides."},{"time":327561,"text":"You use chemicals. You put them into water where they breed."},{"time":330373,"text":"Now in an urban environment, that's extraordinarily difficult."},{"time":333173,"text":"You've got to get your chemical into every puddle,"},{"time":335358,"text":"every birdbath, every tree trunk."},{"time":337606,"text":"It's just not practical."},{"time":340648,"text":"The second way you can do it"},{"time":342164,"text":"is actually trying to kill the insects as they fly around."},{"time":345478,"text":"This is a picture of fogging."},{"time":347704,"text":"Here what someone is doing"},{"time":350149,"text":"is mixing up chemical in a smoke"},{"time":353063,"text":"and basically spreading that through the environment."},{"time":356077,"text":"You could do the same with a space spray."},{"time":359037,"text":"This is really unpleasant stuff,"},{"time":360605,"text":"and if it was any good, we wouldn't have this massive increase"},{"time":363007,"text":"in mosquitos and we wouldn't have this massive increase in dengue fever."},{"time":367663,"text":"So it's not very effective, but it's probably"},{"time":369752,"text":"the best thing we've got at the moment."},{"time":372647,"text":"Having said that, actually, your best form of protection"},{"time":374799,"text":"and my best form of protection is a long-sleeve shirt"},{"time":377184,"text":"and a little bit of DEET to go with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380608,"text":"So let's start again. Let's design a product,"},{"time":384297,"text":"right from the word go, and decide what we want."},{"time":387573,"text":"Well we clearly need something that is effective"},{"time":390168,"text":"at reducing the mosquito population."},{"time":392476,"text":"There's no point in just killing the odd mosquito here and there."},{"time":394908,"text":"We want something that gets that population right the way down"},{"time":398000,"text":"so it can't get the disease transmission."},{"time":401016,"text":"Clearly the product you've got has got to be safe to humans."},{"time":404320,"text":"We are going to use it in and around humans."},{"time":406496,"text":"It has to be safe."},{"time":408059,"text":"We don't want to have a lasting impact on the environment."},{"time":410289,"text":"We don't want to do anything that you can't undo."},{"time":413523,"text":"Maybe a better product comes along in 20, 30 years."},{"time":418616,"text":"Fine. We don't want a lasting environmental impact."},{"time":421490,"text":"We want something that's relatively cheap, or cost-effective,"},{"time":424762,"text":"because there's an awful lot of countries involved,"},{"time":426715,"text":"and some of them are emerging markets,"},{"time":428721,"text":"some of them emerging countries, low-income."},{"time":432283,"text":"And finally, you want something that's species-specific."},{"time":434658,"text":"You want to get rid of this mosquito that spreads dengue,"},{"time":437446,"text":"but you don't really want to get all the other insects."},{"time":440434,"text":"Some are quite beneficial. Some are important to your ecosystem."},{"time":443650,"text":"This one's not. It's invaded you."},{"time":445488,"text":"But you don't want to get all of the insects."},{"time":448170,"text":"You just want to get this one."},{"time":449829,"text":"And most of the time, you'll find this insect"},{"time":452688,"text":"lives in and around your home,"},{"time":454123,"text":"so this -- whatever we do has got to get to that insect."},{"time":458047,"text":"It's got to get into people's houses, into the bedrooms,"},{"time":460430,"text":"into the kitchens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462224,"text":"Now there are two features of mosquito biology"},{"time":465869,"text":"that really help us in this project,"},{"time":467769,"text":"and that is, firstly, males don't bite."},{"time":471641,"text":"It's only the female mosquito that will actually bite you."},{"time":474750,"text":"The male can't bite you, won't bite you,"},{"time":477151,"text":"doesn't have the mouth parts to bite you."},{"time":479454,"text":"It's just the female."},{"time":481113,"text":"And the second is a phenomenon"},{"time":483086,"text":"that males are very, very good at finding females."},{"time":487302,"text":"If there's a male mosquito that you release,"},{"time":489950,"text":"and if there's a female around, that male will find the female."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494793,"text":"So basically, we've used those two factors."},{"time":498611,"text":"So here's a typical situation,"},{"time":500279,"text":"male meets female, lots of offspring."},{"time":502847,"text":"A single female will lay about"},{"time":504576,"text":"up to 100 eggs at a time,"},{"time":506371,"text":"up to about 500 in her lifetime."},{"time":508855,"text":"Now if that male is carrying a gene"},{"time":511876,"text":"which causes the death of the offspring,"},{"time":514494,"text":"then the offspring don't survive,"},{"time":517175,"text":"and instead of having 500 mosquitos running around,"},{"time":520606,"text":"you have none."},{"time":523227,"text":"And if you can put more, I'll call them sterile,"},{"time":526346,"text":"that the offspring will actually die at different stages,"},{"time":529219,"text":"but I'll call them sterile for now."},{"time":530808,"text":"If you put more sterile males out into the environment,"},{"time":534364,"text":"then the females are more likely to find a sterile male"},{"time":537652,"text":"than a fertile one, and you will bring that population down."},{"time":543491,"text":"So the males will go out, they'll look for females,"},{"time":545886,"text":"they'll mate. If they mate successfully, then no offspring."},{"time":549710,"text":"If they don't find a female, then they'll die anyway."},{"time":552713,"text":"They only live a few days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556447,"text":"And that's exactly where we are."},{"time":558681,"text":"So this is technology that was developed"},{"time":560311,"text":"in Oxford University a few years ago."},{"time":562863,"text":"The company itself, Oxitec, we've been working"},{"time":565284,"text":"for the last 10 years, very much on a sort of similar"},{"time":567833,"text":"development pathway that you'd get with a pharmaceutical company."},{"time":571275,"text":"So about 10 years of internal evaluation, testing,"},{"time":575385,"text":"to get this to a state where we think it's actually ready."},{"time":578777,"text":"And then we've gone out into the big outdoors,"},{"time":581264,"text":"always with local community consent,"},{"time":582865,"text":"always with the necessary permits."},{"time":585050,"text":"So we've done field trials now in the Cayman Islands,"},{"time":588113,"text":"a small one in Malaysia,"},{"time":589659,"text":"and two more now in Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593994,"text":"And what's the result?"},{"time":595727,"text":"Well, the result has been very good."},{"time":599035,"text":"In about four months of release,"},{"time":601859,"text":"we've brought that population of mosquitos"},{"time":604155,"text":"— in most cases we're dealing with villages here"},{"time":606698,"text":"of about 2,000, 3,000 people, that sort of size,"},{"time":609970,"text":"starting small —"},{"time":611408,"text":"we've taken that mosquito population down"},{"time":613599,"text":"by about 85 percent in about four months."},{"time":616823,"text":"And in fact, the numbers after that get,"},{"time":618822,"text":"those get very difficult to count, because there just aren't any left."},{"time":622562,"text":"So that's been what we've seen in Cayman,"},{"time":624218,"text":"it's been what we've seen in Brazil"},{"time":627480,"text":"in those trials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629466,"text":"And now what we're doing is we're going through a process"},{"time":631778,"text":"to scale up to a town of about 50,000,"},{"time":634611,"text":"so we can see this work at big scale."},{"time":636984,"text":"And we've got a production unit in Oxford,"},{"time":639771,"text":"or just south of Oxford, where we actually produce these mosquitos."},{"time":643262,"text":"We can produce them,"},{"time":644466,"text":"in a space a bit more than this red carpet,"},{"time":646622,"text":"I can produce about 20 million a week."},{"time":649146,"text":"We can transport them around the world."},{"time":651312,"text":"It's not very expensive, because it's a coffee cup --"},{"time":654334,"text":"something the size of a coffee cup"},{"time":655623,"text":"will hold about three million eggs."},{"time":658950,"text":"So freight costs aren't our biggest problem. (Laughter)"},{"time":662768,"text":"So we've got that. You could call it a mosquito factory."},{"time":666072,"text":"And for Brazil, where we've been doing some trials,"},{"time":669168,"text":"the Brazilian government themselves have now built"},{"time":671056,"text":"their own mosquito factory, far bigger than ours,"},{"time":673488,"text":"and we'll use that for scaling up in Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678963,"text":"There you are. We've sent mosquito eggs."},{"time":681336,"text":"We've separated the males from the females."},{"time":683968,"text":"The males have been put in little pots"},{"time":687618,"text":"and the truck is going down the road"},{"time":689702,"text":"and they are releasing males as they go."},{"time":692666,"text":"It's actually a little bit more precise than that."},{"time":694316,"text":"You want to release them so that"},{"time":695797,"text":"you get good coverage of your area."},{"time":697878,"text":"So you take a Google Map, you divide it up,"},{"time":700669,"text":"work out how far they can fly,"},{"time":702553,"text":"and make sure you're releasing such that you get"},{"time":704528,"text":"coverage of the area, and then you go back,"},{"time":707426,"text":"and within a very short space of time,"},{"time":709200,"text":"you're bringing that population right the way down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712776,"text":"We've also done this in agriculture."},{"time":715208,"text":"We've got several different species of agriculture coming along,"},{"time":719280,"text":"and I'm hoping that soon"},{"time":721188,"text":"we'll be able to get some funding together so we can get back"},{"time":723984,"text":"and start looking at malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727066,"text":"So that's where we stand at the moment,"},{"time":729115,"text":"and I've just got a few final thoughts,"},{"time":731644,"text":"which is that this is another way in which biology"},{"time":735088,"text":"is now coming in to supplement chemistry"},{"time":739077,"text":"in some of our societal advances in this area,"},{"time":742820,"text":"and these biological approaches are coming in"},{"time":745108,"text":"in very different forms,"},{"time":747509,"text":"and when you think about genetic engineering,"},{"time":749831,"text":"we've now got enzymes for industrial processing,"},{"time":752837,"text":"enzymes, genetically engineered enzymes in food."},{"time":755771,"text":"We have G.M. crops, we have pharmaceuticals,"},{"time":758573,"text":"we have new vaccines,"},{"time":759889,"text":"all using roughly the same technology, but with very different outcomes."},{"time":763973,"text":"And I'm in favor, actually. Of course I am."},{"time":767486,"text":"I'm in favor of particularly where the older technologies"},{"time":770382,"text":"don't work well or have become unacceptable."},{"time":773454,"text":"And although the techniques are similar,"},{"time":776811,"text":"the outcomes are very, very different,"},{"time":778352,"text":"and if you take our approach, for example,"},{"time":779866,"text":"and you compare it to, say, G.M. crops,"},{"time":782291,"text":"both techniques are trying to produce a massive benefit."},{"time":786583,"text":"Both have a side benefit,"},{"time":788726,"text":"which is that we reduce pesticide use tremendously."},{"time":792435,"text":"But whereas a G.M. crop is trying to protect the plant,"},{"time":796396,"text":"for example, and give it an advantage,"},{"time":799140,"text":"what we're actually doing is taking the mosquito"},{"time":802235,"text":"and giving it the biggest disadvantage it can possibly have,"},{"time":806324,"text":"rendering it unable to reproduce effectively."},{"time":809308,"text":"So for the mosquito, it's a dead end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812908,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}